00:35.840 --> 00:39.320
The Gospel of St. Luke, chapter 19.

00:41.620 --> 00:47.720
And Jesus entered and passed through Jericho. And, behold, there was a man named Zacchaeus,

00:47.720 --> 00:54.240
which was the chief among the publicans, and he was rich. And he sought to see Jesus, who

00:54.240 --> 01:02.080
he was, and could not for the press, because he was little of stature. And he ran before

01:02.080 --> 01:07.520
and climbed up into a sycamore tree to see him, for he was to pass that way.

01:08.460 --> 01:14.680
And when Jesus came to the place, he looked up and saw him, and said unto him,

01:15.600 --> 01:21.840
Zacchaeus, make haste and come down, for today I must abide at thy house.

01:22.860 --> 01:29.960
And he made haste, and came down, and received him joyfully. And when they saw it, they all

01:29.960 --> 01:35.000
murmured, saying, that he was gone to beguessed with a man that is a sinner.

01:35.900 --> 01:42.720
And Zacchaeus stood and said unto the Lord, Behold, Lord, the half of my goods I give to

01:42.720 --> 01:49.540
the poor. And if I have taken anything from any man by false accusation, I restore him

01:49.540 --> 01:57.680
fourfold. And Jesus said unto him, This day is salvation come to this house, for as much

01:57.680 --> 02:04.860
as he also is a son of Abraham. For the son of man is come to seek and to save that which

02:04.860 --> 02:11.980
was lost. And as they heard these things, he added and spake a parable, because he was

02:11.980 --> 02:16.980
an eye to Jerusalem, and because they thought that the kingdom of God should immediately

02:16.980 --> 02:24.520
appear. He said therefore, A certain nobleman went into a far country to receive for himself

02:24.520 --> 02:31.640
a kingdom, and to return. And he called his ten servants, and delivered them ten pounds,

02:31.800 --> 02:39.520
and said unto them, Occupy till I come. But his citizens hated him, and sent a message

02:40.120 --> 02:46.580
saying, We will not have this man to reign over us. And it came to pass that when he

02:46.580 --> 02:52.160
was returned, having received the kingdom, then he commanded these servants to be called

02:52.160 --> 02:58.220
unto him, to whom he had given the money, that he might know how much every man had

02:58.220 --> 03:06.440
gained by trading. Then came the first, saying, Lord, thy pound hath gained ten pounds. And

03:06.440 --> 03:12.580
he said unto him, Well, thou good servant, because thou hast been faithful in a very

03:12.580 --> 03:20.020
little, have thou authority over ten cities. And the second came, saying, Lord, thy pound

03:20.020 --> 03:28.580
hath gained five pounds. And he said likewise to him, Be thou also over five cities. And

03:28.580 --> 03:34.620
another came, saying, Lord, behold, here is thy pound which I have kept laid up in a napkin.

03:35.180 --> 03:41.860
For I feared thee, because thou art an austere man. Thou takest up that which thou layest

03:41.860 --> 03:49.620
not down, and reapest that thou didst not sow. And he saith unto him, Out of thine own

03:49.620 --> 03:56.140
mouth will I judge thee, thou wicked servant. Thou knewest that I was an austere man, taking

03:56.140 --> 04:04.080
up that I laid not down, and reaping that I did not sow. Wherefore then gavest not thou

04:04.080 --> 04:11.540
my money into the bank, that at my coming I might have required my own with usury? And

04:11.540 --> 04:17.220
he said unto them that stood by, Take from him the pound, and give it to him that hath

04:17.220 --> 04:24.840
ten pounds. And they said unto him, Lord, he hath ten pounds. For I say unto you, that

04:24.840 --> 04:32.180
unto every one which hath shall be given, and from him that hath not, even that he hath

04:32.180 --> 04:38.660
shall be taken away from him. But those mine enemies, which would not that I should reign

04:38.660 --> 04:42.680
over them, bring hither, and slay them before me.

04:44.580 --> 04:51.820
And when he had thus spoken, he went before, ascending up to Jerusalem. And it came to

04:51.820 --> 04:57.900
pass, when he was come nigh to Bethphagy and Bethany, at the mount called the Mount of

04:57.900 --> 05:05.980
Olives, he sent two of his disciples, saying, Go ye into the village over against you, in

05:05.980 --> 05:12.920
the which at your entering ye shall find a colt tide, whereon, yet never man sat, loose

05:12.920 --> 05:20.220
him, and bring him hither. And if any man ask you, Why do ye loose him? thus shall ye

05:20.220 --> 05:23.840
say unto him, Because the Lord hath need of him.

05:24.800 --> 05:30.820
And they that were sent went their way, and found even as he had said unto them. And

05:30.820 --> 05:37.440
as they were loosing the colt, the owners thereof said unto them, Why loose ye the colt?

05:37.800 --> 05:44.640
And they said, The Lord hath need of him. And they brought him to Jesus. And they cast

05:44.640 --> 05:51.080
their garments upon the colt, and they set Jesus thereon. And as he went, they spread

05:51.080 --> 05:57.100
their clothes in the way. And when he was come nigh, even now, at the descent of the

05:57.100 --> 06:02.860
Mount of Olives, the whole multitude of the disciples began to rejoice and praise God

06:02.860 --> 06:08.620
with a loud voice for all the mighty works that they had seen, saying, Blessed be the

06:08.620 --> 06:13.920
King that cometh in the name of the Lord, Peace in heaven, and glory in the highest.

06:14.700 --> 06:21.240
And some of the Pharisees from among the multitude said unto him, Master, rebuke thy disciples.

06:22.240 --> 06:28.380
And he answered and said unto them, I tell you, that if these should hold their peace,

06:28.760 --> 06:34.960
the stones would immediately cry out. And when he was come near, he beheld the city

06:34.960 --> 06:43.460
and wept over it, saying, If thou hadst known even thou, at least in this thy day, the things

06:43.460 --> 06:50.100
which belong unto thy peace. But now they are hid from thine eyes. For the days shall

06:50.100 --> 06:56.060
come upon thee that thine enemies shall cast a trench about thee, and compass thee round,

06:56.500 --> 07:03.040
and keep thee in on every side, and shall lay thee even with the ground, and thy children

07:03.040 --> 07:10.060
within thee. And they shall not leave in thee one stone upon another, because thou knewest

07:10.060 --> 07:17.100
not the time of thy visitation. And he went into the temple, and began to cast out them

07:17.100 --> 07:24.200
that sold therein, and them that bought, saying unto them, It is written, My house is the

07:24.200 --> 07:31.600
house of prayer, but ye have made it a den of thieves. And he taught daily in the temple.

07:32.300 --> 07:37.480
But the chief priests and the scribes and the chief of the people sought to destroy

07:37.480 --> 07:43.860
him, and could not find what they might do, for all the people were very attentive to

07:43.860 --> 07:44.840
hear him.

07:45.880 --> 07:53.220
Chapter 20 And it came to pass that on one of those days, as he taught the people in

07:53.220 --> 08:00.180
the temple, and preached the gospel, the chief priests and the scribes came upon him

08:00.180 --> 08:07.460
with the elders, and spake unto him, saying, Tell us, by what authority dost thou these

08:07.460 --> 08:16.020
things, or who is he that gave thee this authority? And he answered and said unto them, I will

08:16.020 --> 08:23.400
also ask you one thing, and answer me, The baptism of John, was it from heaven or of

08:23.400 --> 08:30.820
men? And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say from heaven, he will say,

08:31.200 --> 08:38.700
Why then believ ye him not? But and if we say of men, all the people will stone us,

08:38.900 --> 08:45.400
for they be persuaded that John was a prophet. And they answered that they could not tell

08:45.400 --> 08:53.860
whence it was. And Jesus said unto them, Neither tell I you by what authority I do these things.

08:54.620 --> 09:01.620
Then began he to speak to the people this parable. A certain man planted a vineyard

09:01.620 --> 09:09.440
and led it forth to husbandmen, and went into a far country for a long time. And at the

09:09.440 --> 09:15.420
season he sent a servant to the husbandmen that they should give him of the fruit of

09:15.420 --> 09:22.960
the vineyard. But the husbandmen beat him and sent him away empty. And again he sent

09:22.960 --> 09:29.000
another servant, and they beat him also, and entreated him shamefully, and sent him

09:29.000 --> 09:37.640
away empty. And again he sent a third, and they wounded him also, and cast him out. Then

09:37.640 --> 09:45.140
said the Lord of the vineyard, What shall I do? I will send my beloved son. It may be

09:45.140 --> 09:52.100
they will reverence him when they see him. But when the husbandmen saw him, they reasoned

09:52.100 --> 09:58.340
among themselves, saying, This is the heir. Come, let us kill him, that the inheritance

09:58.340 --> 10:06.100
may be ours. So they cast him out of the vineyard and killed him. What therefore shall the Lord

10:06.100 --> 10:11.620
of the vineyard do unto them? He shall come and destroy these husbandmen, and shall give

10:11.620 --> 10:17.900
the vineyard to others. And when they heard it, they said, God forbid. And he beheld them

10:17.900 --> 10:25.320
and said, What is this then that is written? The stone which the builders rejected, the

10:25.320 --> 10:32.040
same is become the head of the corner. Whosoever shall fall upon that stone shall be broken.

10:33.040 --> 10:41.020
But on whomsoever it shall fall, it will grind him to powder. And the chief priests and the

10:41.020 --> 10:47.280
scribes the same hour sought to lay hands on him, and they feared the people, for they

10:47.280 --> 10:54.340
perceived that he had spoken this parable against them. And they watched him, and sent

10:54.340 --> 11:00.160
forth spies which should feign themselves, just men, that they might take hold of his

11:00.160 --> 11:06.500
words, that so they might deliver him unto the power and authority of the governor. And

11:06.500 --> 11:13.340
they asked him, saying, Master, we know that thou sayest and teachest rightly, neither

11:13.340 --> 11:20.840
acceptest thou the person of any, but teachest the way of God truly. Is it lawful for us

11:20.840 --> 11:27.760
to give tribute unto Caesar, or no? But he perceived their craftiness, and said unto

11:27.760 --> 11:37.200
them, Why tempt ye me? show me a penny, whose image and superscription hath it? They answered

11:37.200 --> 11:44.620
and said, Caesar's. And he said unto them, Render therefore unto Caesar the things which

11:44.620 --> 11:51.640
be Caesar's, and unto God the things which be God's. And they could not take hold of

11:51.640 --> 11:57.780
his words before the people, and they marveled at his answer, and held their peace.

11:59.860 --> 12:05.600
Then came to him certain of the Sadducees, which deny that there is any resurrection,

12:05.600 --> 12:13.580
and they asked him, saying, Master, Moses wrote unto us, if any man's brother die having

12:13.580 --> 12:19.640
a wife, and he die without children, that his brother should take his wife and raise

12:19.640 --> 12:26.140
up seed unto his brother. There were therefore seven brethren, and the first took a wife,

12:26.460 --> 12:32.620
and died without children, and the second took her to wife, and he died childless, and

12:32.620 --> 12:38.840
the third took her, and in like manner the seven also, and they left no children, and

12:38.840 --> 12:45.940
died. Last of all the woman died also. Therefore in the resurrection whose wife of them is

12:45.940 --> 12:53.520
she? For seven had her to wife. And Jesus answering said unto them, The children of

12:53.520 --> 13:00.060
this world marry and are given in marriage. But they which shall be accounted worthy to

13:00.060 --> 13:06.400
obtain that world, and the resurrection from the dead, neither marry nor are given in marriage.

13:07.360 --> 13:13.940
Neither can they die any more, for they are equal unto the angels, and are the children

13:13.940 --> 13:21.540
of God, being the children of the resurrection. Now that the dead are raised, even Moses showed

13:21.540 --> 13:27.580
at the bush, when he called the Lord the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the

13:27.580 --> 13:35.240
God of Jacob. For he is not a God of the dead, but of the living, for all live unto him.

13:36.880 --> 13:45.180
Then certain of the scribes answering said, Master, thou hast well said. And after that

13:45.180 --> 13:53.800
they durst not ask him any questions at all. And he said unto them, How say they that Christ

13:53.800 --> 14:01.380
is David's son? And David himself saith in the book of Psalms, The Lord said unto my

14:01.380 --> 14:08.940
Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, till I make thine enemies thy footstool. David therefore

14:09.160 --> 14:17.540
calleth him Lord. How is he then his son? Then in the audience of all the people he

14:17.540 --> 14:25.500
said unto his disciples, Beware of the scribes which desire to walk in long robes, and love

14:25.500 --> 14:31.320
greetings in the markets, and the highest seats in the synagogues, and the chief rooms

14:31.320 --> 14:39.760
at feasts, which devour widows' houses, and for a show make long prayers. The same shall

14:39.760 --> 14:41.800
receive greater damnation.

14:43.180 --> 14:49.680
End of chapter 20 of The Gospel According to St. Luke in the Authorized Version, commonly

14:49.680 --> 14:52.640
known as the King James Translation.

